Implemented the fix in source only.

Changed files:
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/SerializationDelegatingTypeAdapter.java`
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/Gson.java`
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/bind/TreeTypeAdapter.java`
- `gson/src/main/java/com/google/gson/internal/bind/TypeAdapterRuntimeTypeWrapper.java`

What changed:
- Added an internal interface for adapters which delegate serialization.
- Made `Gson.FutureTypeAdapter` expose its resolved serialization delegate.
- Made `TreeTypeAdapter` expose its effective serialization delegate when serialization is delegated.
- Updated `TypeAdapterRuntimeTypeWrapper` to determine whether an adapter is effectively reflective by unwrapping serialization-delegating adapters before applying the reflective/custom preference logic.

Validation:
- Compiled sources with `javac --release 8`.
- Ran a local reproducer for the cyclic `Base` / `Sub` case; output is now:

```json
{"f":{"i":2}}
```
